text_copy_1853875258.text: Meet Altra's New  elite  Athlete, Jacky Hunt-Broersma.

text_copy.text:
Jacky is not only a runner, but a cancer survivor, mother, and a decorated amputee ultramarathoner. She has been a trailblazer for all female and disabled runners within the community with her record-breaking talent.

03-14-2023

text_copy_copy_copy__935922704.text:
Where are you from?

I currently live in Arizona. We moved to Arizona from North Carolina where we lived for 5 years. I was born and raised in South Africa though. We love traveling and seeing the world and I have been very fortunate to have lived in the Netherlands (7 years), the UK (13 years) and now the USA.

text_copy_copy_copy_1612682511.text:
How did you get into running?

I started running six and a half years ago because my husband is a runner, and I was curious to see if I could do it as an amputee. I wasn't a runner before losing my leg, so this was an exciting new challenge for me. It definitely was challenging because I had to run with a running prosthetic, but I am so glad I had the courage to give it a shot, because running truly did change my life.

text_copy_copy_copy__1370362781.text:
What do you love about running?

I love how it makes me feel. Free, strong, and fearless. it has also given me the confidence to be who I am and given me a love for my body. I was often ashamed of what I looked like as an amputee and running helped me accept myself for who I am.

text_copy_copy_copy_.text:
Where do you train the most?

I mostly train on the trails, but I will mix it up with some road and treadmill running, depending on time, because often I need to fit in my run between kids' school drop off and school homework etc.

text_copy_copy_copy__1644895230.text:
What running milestone are you looking forward to this year?

I am looking forward to building my dream of running Western States. I have a few 100 milers coming up which are all Western States qualifiers.

text_copy_copy_copy__1285042581.text:
What's your go-to Altra Shoe?

My favorite shoe for trail running is the Lone Peak 7 and for road running I have always loved the Escalante; but I am loving the new Rivera 3 so I think that might be my new favorite road shoe.
